title: Grateful Dead Live at Zoo Amphitheater on 1982-08-01
lineage: Playback: Nakamichi LX-5 ->Marantz PMD 661|SD card 24/96Processing: SD->Audacity (Windows 7)-> CDWav editor ->TLH (flac)Taped by; Executive Crew: Kyle Holbrook & Olvy JohnsonTransferred by Kyle Holbrook
taper: Executive Crew: Kyle Holbrook & Olvy Johnson
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, CC Rider, Tennessee Jed, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> Iko Iko-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Thanks for new recording This show had a lot of potential when looking at the tour before it started. I know myself and my crew thought this would be the show to attend along with the Rocks
1st you can hear a lot of crowd noise not so much yet in the 2nd although only a portion into it. I love this Aiko it is long and slower then the years to follow when it became a staple. back during this time frame we all talked about Aiko being a song to hear.  
 Love the Wheel Playing Black Peter round and round " let all the animals out"  Bobby was in good form on this summer tour with scats and adlibs.   Not bad sound at all here
